radiographic_examinations.findings: High signal intensity within the body of the pancreas and to a lesser extent the head. Heterogenous enhancement of the pancreatic parenchyma with decreased enhancement in the pancreatic body compared to the tail. Some heterogenous enhancement is noted in the head and uncinate process. Some free fluid is noted in the right subhepatic space and in the paracolic gutters bilaterally. No significant lymphadenopathy, normal liver, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, bowel, and gallbladder.
